descript.abstract: U.S. Populated Place Points represents populated places that include census designated places, consolidated cities, and incorporated places within United States identified by the U.S. Census Bureau.
descript.purpose: U.S. Populated Place Points provides locations for populated places including attributes - name, FIPS code, Census class, area, and selected demographic data.
descript.supplinf: Largest scale when displaying the data: 1:250,000.

enttyp.enttypd: The points represent concentrations of population that include census designated places, consolidated cities, and incorporated places identified by the U.S. Census Bureau.

attrdomv.udom: Sequential unique whole numbers that are automatically generated.

attr.attrdef: The class of the populated place.

edom.edomvd: In Connecticut, New Jersey, and Pennsylvania, an incorporated place.

Census designated place - A statistical entity, defined for each decennial census according to Census Bureau guidelines, comprising a densely settled concentration of population that is not within an incorporated place, but is locally identified by a name.

An incorporated place in 49 States and the District of Columbia. In 20 States, some or all cities are not part of any minor civil division, and the Census Bureau also treats these as county subdivisions, statistically equivalent to minor civil divisions.
The portion of the consolidated city minus the incorporated places. For statistical purposes, these entities are treated as statistically equivalent to a place and have no legal basis or functions.
An incorporated place in 30 States. In New Jersey, Pennsylvania, and South Dakota, the Census Bureau treats these towns as the equivalent of a minor civil division.
An incorporated place in 20 States. The Census Bureau treats all villages in New Jersey, South Dakota, and Wisconsin, and some villages in Ohio as county subdivisions.

attr.attrdef: The two-letter abbreviation for the state in which the populated place is located.
attr.attrdefs: Department of Commerce, National Institute of Standards and Technology

codesetd.codesets: National Institute of Standards and Technology

attr.attrdef: The FIPS code (two-digit number) for the state in which the populated place is located.
attr.attrdefs: Department of Commerce, National Institute of Standards and Technology

codesetd.codesets: National Institute of Standards and Technology

attr.attrdefs: Department of Commerce, National Institute of Standards and Technology
attr.attrdef: The FIPS code (five-digit number) for the populated place within a State.

codesetd.codesets: National Institute of Standards and Technology

attr.attrdef: The 2000 housing unit counts of the populated place.
The 2000 population of the populated place.
The code for the population class of the populated place.
The area in square miles of the populated place which is land.
The area in square miles of the populated place which is water.

citeinfo.title: Summary File 1 (SF1)
citeinfo.othercit: The Summary File 1 (SF1) data is based on the 2000 Census of Population. The geospatial data is calculated from the latitude/longitude coordinate attributes.

procstep.procdesc: The following steps were performed by ESRI for Data & Maps 2002: Created a data set by extracting populated places from U.S. Census Bureau 2000 Summary File 1 (SF1). Ran ArcView GIS command Add Event Theme on the data set to create the point location centroids shapefile. Reformatted attributes and finalized attribute order. Created ArcGIS® layer file (.lyr), projection file (.prj), and spatial indices. Converted the data set to SDC.
The following steps were performed by ESRI: Changed CLASS = 'CDP' to CLASS = 'Census Designated Place'. Made CLASS attribute title case.

The following steps were performed by ESRI: Renamed attributes AREANAME to NAME, POPULATION to POP2000, and POP_CL to POP_CLASS. Reduced the attribute widths for NAME and CLASS. Changed the CLASS attribute value "CDP" to "Census Designated Place".

horizpa.horizpar: The geospatial part of this data set was calculated from latitude/longitude coordinates from the U.S. Census Bureau 2000 Summary File 1 (SF1). The horizontal positional accuracy is unknown.

dataqual.logic: The shapefile is converted to SDC (Smart Data Compression) format using either ESRI SDC Data Development Kit Professional 2 (DDKP2) or tools in ArcGIS. The SDC data set is then loaded into ArcSDE® to verify and validate the geometry.
dataqual.complete: After processing, the data set is checked for drawing display and number of records and file sizes compared with source materials.
